The paper discusses deep learning techniques and their successes and limitations, which are primarily studied in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on overfitting, which is a common issue in machine learning models, and proposes a new algorithm to avoid it. This makes the paper relevant to sub-categories such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses natural language processing (NLP) as one of the tasks where deep learning has achieved breakthroughs, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
